<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80b5ecb0-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s3302"><num value="3302">§ 3302.</num><heading> Prohibition on construction of buildings except by Administrator of General Services</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Only the Administrator of General Services may construct a public building. The Administrator shall construct a public building in accordance with this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80b85cb1-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1158">116 Stat. 1158</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
